{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"783bb0b1-1427-4dd5-a432-0f839f0943d2","content":"The migration is straightforward. In your project file, **remove** (or set to `false`) the `UseVSTest` property:\n\n```xml\n<!-- Before -->\n<Project Sdk=\"MSTest.Sdk/3.8.0\">\n  <PropertyGroup>\n    <UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>\n  </PropertyGroup>\n</Project>\n\n<!-- After -->\n<Project Sdk=\"MSTest.Sdk/3.8.0\">\n  <PropertyGroup>\n    <!-- UseVSTest removed — Microsoft.Testing.Platform is the default -->\n  </PropertyGroup>\n</Project>\n```\n\n**Key things to know:**\n\n1. **MSTest.Sdk 3.4+** defaults to Microsoft.Testing.Platform, so simply deleting `<UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>` is enough.\n2. **CLI changes** — use `dotnet test` as before, but the underlying runner is now different. You can also run the test executable directly (`./MyTests.exe`).\n3. **`.runsettings`** — most VSTest runsettings are still supported, but platform-specific extensions may need updating.\n4. **Test Explorer in VS** — works with VS 17.8+. Ensure you're on a compatible version.\n5. **If you use VSTest-specific adapters or extensions**, verify they have Microsoft.Testing.Platform equivalents.\n\nThat's it — remove one line and you're on the new platform.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"bc2bd58a-b63a-4f0b-b427-c4db1834b219","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The working directory is empty and there's no project-specific content to reference. Let me answer based on my knowledge of MSTest.Sdk and the migration from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform.","outputTokens":400,"requestId":"9823:35D604:180C48:1F3507:69FFD828"},"id":"97446df8-7155-4126-9a01-eed4587bda48","timestamp":"2026-05-10T00:58:25.068Z","parentId":"57608964-3b8d-47ca-ba8d-fa5ab5e54c24"}
